The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Lack of cooperation by officials of the state health department and NRS Medical College and Hospital proved a stumbling block in the investigation of the medicine scam, police claimed on Sunday.   ccording to an officer of Muchipara police station, the health department has not provided investigators with a list of life saving drugs sent to state-run hospitals in the past three years. Unless we get the list, we cant gauge the extent of the scam, he said.  he police are also awaiting a list of medicines given to poor patients in the past few years from the NRS authorities. The investigators have found discrepancies in the number of medicines sent to the hospital and those reaching the poor patients.   hree employees of the hospital, including the nurse-in-charge, have been arrested for allegedly smuggling medicines and consumables out of the hospital. The hospital authorities denied the allegation.    An eye bank was inaugurated at MP Birla Eye Clinic on Loudon Street on Sunday. The bank with a list of 100 existing donors is the third in the city. It has been allowed to start a Hospital Cornea Retrieval Programme, under which grief counsellors from the bank will speak to relatives of donors who die at Sambhunath Pandit Hospital.     Cellphones worth several thousand rupees were stolen from a shop on Netaji Subhas Road, under Bantra police station in Howrah, on Saturday night. Police said more than one burglar had entered the shop after making a hole in the concrete wall at the back of the store. Last week, cellphone handsets were stolen from a shop in Salkia, Howrah, after cutting open the shutter.    Neighbours and relatives of a 59-year-old woman, who died at a nursing home in Thakurpukur, attacked employees and broke furniture on the premises on Sunday night, alleging medical negligence. Rita Halder had been admitted to the hospital on Friday night. She underwent a gall bladder surgery on Saturday.    An 18-year-old resident of Shibpur in Howrah, Chayan Chaudhury, died after a truck hit his cycle from behind on Drainage Canal Road around 11pm on Saturday. Police said local people chased the truck and tried to set it on fire. The driver and helper fled. The body has been sent for post-mortem.     The body of an unidentified woman in her 20s was found lying near the rail tracks between Bally and Uttarpara on Sunday morning. A Government Railway Police (GRP) officer said that they were not sure whether the woman was killed and dumped on the track or had committed suicide. The body has been sent for post-mortem.    A Bajaj Pulsar motorcycle was stolen from Mominpur Road on Saturday. Police said the bike was parked on the road. Owner Kamar Khan has lodged a complaint.    The owner of a godown on MG Road was arrested after 120 jars of fake lubricants and nearly 3,000 holograms, stickers, buckets and caps of a reputable brand were recovered from the premises on Saturday evening. Cops said the raid was conducted after they received a complaint from an oil company.     Eastern Railway will run a pair of special trains between Sealdah and Ghutiari Sharif on August 3 and August 4 night. The train from Sealdah will leave at 11.50pm and the one from Ghutiari Sharif will leave at 3.45am.             
